POST

/v1/workspaces/:id/saml/service-providers/:sspId/test

Trigger IdP-initiated SSO test (returns assertion for inspection)



4.2 POST /v1/workspaces/:id/saml/service-providers

Accepts either a metadata XML document (preferred) or manual field configuration. Validates the document, registers the SAML client in Keycloak, persists metadata to the control plane database.



// Option A: Metadata XML upload

{

  "name": "Salesforce Production",

  "registration_mode": "metadata_xml",

  "metadata_xml": "<EntityDescriptor xmlns=\"urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:metadata\" .../>",

  "name_id_format": "email",

  "sign_assertions": true,

  "encrypt_assertions": false,

  "attribute_mappings": [

    { "keycloak_attribute": "email", "saml_attribute_name": "email", "saml_attribute_format": "Basic", "required": true }

  ]

}



// Option B: Manual configuration

{

  "name": "Custom SP",

  "registration_mode": "manual",

  "entity_id": "https://app.customer.com/saml/metadata",

  "acs_url": "https://app.customer.com/saml/acs",

  "slo_url": "https://app.customer.com/saml/slo",

  "name_id_format": "persistent",

  "sp_certificate": "-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\nMIIC...\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----",

  "sign_assertions": true,

  "encrypt_assertions": true,

  "attribute_mappings": []

}



// Response 201

{

  "saml_sp": {

    "id": "ssp_8ab3c2",

    "workspace_id": "wsp_c91b12",

    "name": "Salesforce Production",

    "entity_id": "https://salesforce.com/saml/metadata",

    "acs_url": "https://customer.my.salesforce.com/services/saml2/acs",

    "name_id_format": "email",

    "status": "active",

    "idp_metadata_url": "https://id.foundry-iam.com/realms/tnt_2f8a1d/protocol/saml/descriptor",

    "created_at": "2026-02-28T12:00:00Z"

  }

}



4.3 GET /v1/workspaces/:id/saml/idp-metadata

Returns the Keycloak realm's SAML IdP metadata XML. This is what customers give to their Service Provider (Salesforce, Workday, etc.) to configure the trust relationship. The endpoint proxies directly from Keycloak.



// Response 200

Content-Type: application/xml



<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<EntityDescriptor xmlns="urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:metadata"

  entityID="https://id.foundry-iam.com/realms/tnt_2f8a1d">

  <IDPSSODescriptor

    WantAuthnRequestsSigned="false"

    protocolSupportEnumeration="urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:protocol">

    <KeyDescriptor use="signing">

      <!-- Realm signing certificate -->

    </KeyDescriptor>

    <SingleLogoutService

      Binding="urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:bindings:HTTP-Redirect"

      Location="https://id.foundry-iam.com/realms/tnt_2f8a1d/protocol/saml"/>

    <SingleSignOnService

      Binding="urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:bindings:HTTP-POST"

      Location="https://id.foundry-iam.com/realms/tnt_2f8a1d/protocol/saml"/>

    <SingleSignOnService

      Binding="urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:bindings:HTTP-Redirect"

      Location="https://id.foundry-iam.com/realms/tnt_2f8a1d/protocol/saml"/>

  </IDPSSODescriptor>

</EntityDescriptor>





SECTION 5

Keycloak Admin API Operations





When the control plane receives a SAML SP registration request, it executes the following sequence against the Keycloak Admin REST API. This is the core provisioning logic.



5.1 SP Registration Sequence

Step

Keycloak Admin API Call

Notes

1

POST /admin/realms/{realm}/clients

Create SAML client with protocol=saml

2

PUT /admin/realms/{realm}/clients/{id}

Set entityId, baseUrl, attributes (saml.*), redirectUris

3

POST /admin/realms/{realm}/clients/{id}/protocol-mappers/models

Add attribute mapper for each mapping in attribute_mappings

4

GET /admin/realms/{realm}/clients/{id}/installation/providers/saml-idp-descriptor

Retrieve and store IdP metadata

5

Store in control_plane DB

Persist all metadata to saml_service_providers table



5.2 SAML Client Configuration Object (Keycloak)

// Keycloak client representation for SAML

{

  "clientId": "ssp_8ab3c2",

  "protocol": "saml",

  "enabled": true,

  "frontchannelLogout": true,

  "attributes": {

    "saml.authnstatement": "true",

    "saml.server.signature": "true",

    "saml.signature.algorithm": "RSA_SHA256",

    "saml.assertion.signature": "true",

    "saml.encrypt": "false",

    "saml.client.signature": "false",

    "saml_assertion_consumer_url_post": "https://customer.my.salesforce.com/services/saml2/acs",

    "saml_single_logout_service_url_redirect": "https://customer.my.salesforce.com/services/saml2/slo",

    "saml_name_id_format": "urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:1.1:nameid-format:emailAddress"

  },

  "redirectUris": ["https://customer.my.salesforce.com/*"],

  "baseUrl": "https://customer.my.salesforce.com"

}





SECTION 6

Portal UI — New Pages & Components





6.1 New Portal Routes

Route

Page

Purpose

/saml

SAMLList.tsx

List all registered SAML Service Providers for the workspace

/saml/new

SAMLNew.tsx

Register new SP — XML upload tab + manual config tab

/saml/:id

SAMLDetail.tsx

SP details, attribute mappings editor, IdP metadata download

/saml/:id/test

SAMLTest.tsx

Trigger and inspect IdP-initiated test assertion



6.2 SAML Registration Page (SAMLNew.tsx) — UX Spec

Two registration modes presented as tabs. Metadata XML upload must be the default and prominently recommended — it is less error-prone than manual config.



Tab 1 — 'Upload Metadata (Recommended)': File upload input + paste textarea for metadata XML. On paste/upload, auto-parse and display extracted fields (entityId, ACS URL, signing cert) for confirmation before submission. Show a validation badge: green if metadata is valid XML + contains required fields, red with specific error if not.

Tab 2 — 'Manual Configuration': Form fields for entity_id, acs_url, slo_url (optional), name_id_format (dropdown), sp_certificate (textarea with PEM hint).

Both tabs: Name field (required), attribute mapping section (add/remove rows of keycloak_attr → saml_attr), sign/encrypt toggles.

Submit button disabled until validation passes.



6.3 SAML Detail Page (SAMLDetail.tsx) — UX Spec

Header: SP name, entity ID, status badge, created date.

'Give This to Your SP' section: Display IdP metadata URL with copy button. Download IdP Metadata XML button (calls GET /v1/workspaces/:id/saml/idp-metadata, triggers browser download).

Configuration section: read-only view of ACS URL, SLO URL, NameID format, sign/encrypt settings. Edit button opens modal.

Attribute Mappings section: editable table of keycloak → SAML attribute mappings. Save changes calls PATCH endpoint.

Danger zone: Delete SP (confirmation modal with SP name typed).



6.4 Integration Guide Content (Inline on Detail Page)

A collapsible 'How to configure your SP' section with step-by-step instructions for the most common SPs. Written in plain language, not assumed knowledge.



SP

Integration Steps Summary

Salesforce

Setup → Single Sign-On Settings → New → SAML Enabled → paste IdP metadata fields

Google Workspace

Admin Console → Apps → Web and mobile apps → Add SAML app → upload IdP metadata XML

Microsoft 365 / Azure AD

Azure Portal → Enterprise Applications → New → Non-gallery → Set up single sign-on → SAML

Generic SP

Provide IdP metadata XML URL. Configure ACS URL, EntityID, NameID format as shown above.





SECTION 7

Test Matrix





7.1 Functional Tests

Test ID

Scenario

Expected Result

SAML-001

Register SP via valid metadata XML

SP created in KC, ssp_ record in DB, 201 response with idp_metadata_url

SAML-002

Register SP via manual config

Same as SAML-001

SAML-003

Upload invalid XML to metadata endpoint

422 error: metadata_xml_invalid with specific parse error

SAML-004

Upload metadata missing ACS URL

422 error: acs_url_missing

SAML-005

SP-initiated SSO flow end-to-end

User authenticates at KC, receives SAML assertion at ACS URL, assertion is valid XML-DSig

SAML-006

IdP-initiated SSO flow

Portal triggers assertion push to SP, SP accepts

SAML-007

Single Logout — SP-initiated

User logout at SP triggers SLO to KC, KC terminates session

SAML-008

Single Logout — IdP-initiated

User logout at KC portal triggers SLO to SP ACS

SAML-009

Attribute mapping in assertion

email, firstName, roles appear in assertion attributes as configured

SAML-010

Download IdP metadata XML

Valid XML document returned, parses against SAML metadata schema

SAML-011

Delete SP

KC client removed, DB record deleted, subsequent SSO attempts rejected

SAML-012

Duplicate entityId registration

409 error: entity_id_already_registered

SAML-013

Tenant isolation — SP in realm A cannot be accessed from realm B token

403 Forbidden



7.2 Security Tests

Assertion signature validation: reject unsigned assertions if signing required

Replay attack: reject assertion with duplicate ID within session window

Clock skew: reject assertions with NotBefore/NotOnOrAfter outside 5-minute skew window

XML signature wrapping attack: Keycloak handles this natively — verify with malformed assertion

Cross-tenant access: token from workspace A cannot register or view SPs in workspace B



7.3 Recommended Test Tooling

Tool

Purpose

SAML Tracer

Firefox/Chrome extension — inspect raw SAML assertion XML in browser

SAML DevTools (samltool.io)

Online tool to decode and validate SAML assertions

SimpleSAMLphp Test SP

Docker image: kristophjunge/test-saml-idp — usable as a mock SP for integration tests

Keycloak SAML Tester

Built into Keycloak Admin Console under client → Client Scopes → Evaluate





SECTION 8

Implementation Plan — 7 Days





Day

Focus

Deliverable

Day 1

Database + Keycloak research

saml_service_providers migration applied. Keycloak Admin API tested manually for SAML client creation. Postman collection of all SAML admin calls.

Day 2

Control plane — registration endpoint

POST /v1/workspaces/:id/saml/service-providers works for both metadata and manual modes. SP visible in Keycloak Admin Console.

Day 3

Control plane — remaining endpoints

GET list, GET detail, PATCH, DELETE, GET idp-metadata all implemented and tested.

Day 4

Attribute mapping service

Mapper creation in Keycloak on registration. PATCH endpoint updates mappers. Assertions contain correct attributes.

Day 5

Portal UI — SAML list + registration

SAMLList and SAMLNew pages wired to API. XML upload with client-side validation. Manual config form.

Day 6

Portal UI — detail + integration guide

SAMLDetail page complete. IdP metadata download. Attribute mapping editor. SP-specific guides.

Day 7

End-to-end test + documentation

Full SSO flow tested with mock SP. Test matrix executed. Docs site updated with SAML section.



Pre-condition

The MVP platform must be stable and deployed before starting this feature. SAML cannot be developed or tested without working Keycloak realms and tenant provisioning.



8.1 Plan Limits — What Is NOT in Scope

SAML SP mode (Keycloak acting as SP to an external IdP like Azure AD) — this is covered by the Custom Federation spec

SAML metadata auto-refresh via scheduled polling of metadata_url — defer to Phase 3

SAML attribute value transformation (e.g., reformatting date fields) — defer to Phase 3

Encrypted assertions (encrypt_assertions=true) — the API accepts the field but encryption is disabled in Phase 2; enable in Phase 3 after testing with real SPs




End of SAML 2.0 Extension Specification
